CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1965, pg. 16, reads: "Village Vanguards - Vann Harris (center) is the leader of the Village Vanguards, who are one of the fastest growing musical groups around. Young Harris is flanked by other members of his popular aggregation. - Harris Photo."The members of the Village Vanguards are: Ira Vann Harris on drums, Leonard Goins lead guitar, Eugene Smith bass guitar, Art Nance tenor saxophone, Morris Jefferson trumpet, and Wayne Boykin vocals.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Village Vanguards band wearing matching suits and neckties, including drummer Ira Vann Harris seated in center, and Leonard Goins, Eugene Smith, Art Nance, Morris Jefferson, and Wayne Boykin, posed on plastic covered seat in front of light colored curtain
